All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Action
The Action interface provides a blueprint for all the action related subclasses that implements this interface.
ActionCapable
The ActionCapable interface provides a blueprint for all the action related subclasses that implements this interface.
AddBalanceAction
The AddBalanceAction class is used to allow the user to input the amount of money they want to enter into their account, as well as the payment method that they would like to use.
AddBookingAction
The AddBookingAction class is used to allow the user to add a booking to their bookings list.
ApplePay
This class is one of the payment option that the user can choose from.
Application
The main file to start the application.
Booking
The booking class represents individual bookings of vehicles that can be made by the user.
BookingSystem
The BookingSystem class handles most of the displays that the user will be viewing, it will also stop displaying once the user exits the system.
ConfirmAction
The ConfirmAction class allows users to confirm their bookings, which decreases their balance base on the bookings in their bookings list, as well as clears their bookings list after.
DisplayBookingAction
The DisplayBookingAction class allows the user to see all the vehicles that they have booked.
EngineType
This provides ENUM types for the engine types.
ExitAction
The ExitAction class allows the user to exit the system.
GooglePay
This class is one of the payment option that the user can choose from.
Menu
The Menu class generates all the menu options for the system.
Payment
An abstract class that provides a blueprint for all payment options
RemoveBookingAction
The RemoveBookingAction class allows user to remove a booking of their choice.
Sedan
The Sedan class is a subclass of Vehicle
SUV
The SUV is a subclass of Vehicle
Truck
The Truck is a subclass of Vehicle
User
The user class represents the user of the system and tracks their balance and bookings, as well an attribute to exit the system.
Utilty
The utility class stores functions that may be used in any other classes.
Vehicle
The Vehicle abstract class provides a blueprint for all vehicles to extend
ViewBalanceAction
The ViewBalanceAction class allows user to view the current balance that they have.
